Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Conán . In historical times, the name was borne by a 7th-century saint, bishop of the Isle of Man.  Sir Arthur Conan Doyle  (  1859–1930 ), creator of  Sherlock Holmes , was born in Edinburgh, of Irish stock. The science-fiction creation Conan the Destroyer owes more to the villain of legend than to the bishop or the writer. For the most part this name is of Irish origin; however, it was in use in Yorkshire, especially among the Askes and the Bartons, from the 12th to the 16th centuries. In this case, the name was derived from Conan, Earl of Richmond, and is of Breton origin."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":5,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":14,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":49,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":80,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Conan de Multon was born in 1210, in Letheringsett, Norfolk, England, his father, Elias Multon, was 27 and his mother, Theophania Musard, was 23. He married Ada De Moreville about 1238, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1301, in Norfolk, England, at the age of 91."},"et":{"1210–1301":"1210–1301","1214–Female":"1214–Surnud","1230–1276":"1230–1276","1245–1288":"1245–1288","1183–Male":"1183–Surnud","1188–Female":"1188–Surnud","1230":"1230","1183":"1183","1290":"1290","Abt 1230":"umbes 1230","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1288":"1288","1210":"1210","about 1238":"umbes 1238","1276":"1276","1188":"1188","Letheringsett, Norfolk, England":"Letheringsett, Norfolk, England","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Lodie, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Hunslet, Yorkshire, England":"Hunslet, Yorkshire, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1210–1301":"1210–1301","1214–Female":"1214–Kuollut","1230–1276":"1230–1276","1245–1288":"1245–1288","1183–Male":"1183–Kuollut","1188–Female":"1188–Kuollut","1230":"1230","1183":"1183","1290":"1290","Abt 1230":"noin 1230","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1288":"1288","1210":"1210","about 1238":"noin 1238","1276":"1276","1188":"1188","Letheringsett, Norfolk, England":"Letheringsett, Norfolk, England","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Lodie, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Hunslet, Yorkshire, England":"Hunslet, Yorkshire, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1210–1301":"1210–1301","1214–Female":"1214–Décédée","1230